<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION> suspended service on its two A320 aircraft as of midnight Sunday, hours after a new <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> France </ORGANIZATION> plane of the same type crashed during an air show and killed at least three people. The narrow-bodied short-to-medium-range A320 jet entered commercial service in April, and <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION> took possession of its second this month. Air France took delivery Thursday of the plane that crashed Sunday. <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION> announced it was suspending both its A320s from routes between <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>'s <LOCATION> Gatwick </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> and various European destinations starting at midnight. `` Following discussions with <ORGANIZATION> Airbus </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Civil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aviation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Authority </ORGANIZATION>, we have decided to suspend the A320 services as a precautionary measure pending further information on the cause of today's accident,'' an airline spokeswoman said. She said alternative planes had been arranged and she did not anticipate any cancellations of flights. She was not identified, in keeping with British practice. The Airbus A320 received its certification Feb. 26. The A320 was conceived and certified for flight by a two-member crew, eliminating the navigator. Early this year, pilots and flight engineers of <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inter </ORGANIZATION>, the largest French airline, called a series of strikes to protest the use of only two cockpit members in A320s, saying it was unsafe. According to witnesses, the <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> France </ORGANIZATION> plane, taking part in a show in eastern <LOCATION> France </LOCATION> near the <LOCAT